This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it focuses on improving the conceptual indexing process for information retrieval. Additionally, the use of word embedding and vector-based measures are common techniques used in information retrieval research. 

The paper also touches on natural language processing (NLP) concepts such as word vectors and similarity measures, which are commonly studied in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. 

The use of vector-based measures and machine learning techniques to build concept vectors also aligns with the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Finally, the use of word embedding techniques such as Word2Vec and GloVe falls under the Deep Learning (cs.DL) sub-category, which is also a likely fit for this paper.
